  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 23 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 8 critical, 9 high, 8 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 14 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, snow / blowing snow and low cloud base  — most notably around Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP). Network hotspots: Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Grenoble Alpes Isère (GNB/LFLS), Berlin Brandenburg Willy Brandt (BER/EDDB), Hamburg Helmut Schmidt (HAM/EDDH), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH) and 18 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and thunderstorm / convective risk. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Berlin Brandenburg Willy Brandt (BER/EDDB), Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP), Debrecen (DEB/LHDC) and 9 others.",
